page.par:
Units with a factor of 10-6 normally written with the greek letter μ (mu), are written
with a normal latin "u" instead, so "um" stands for micrometer, and "uA" for microAmpere.
Other prefixes are as normal: (p, 10-12;
		     n, 10-9;
 		     u, 10-6;
             m, 10-3;
             c, 10-2;
             K, 103;
             M, 106;
             G, 109)
although certain intermediate ones (d for deci, h for hecto etc) will not be understood.
Get in touch if you really want them.
